title: Sacred Monkey Forest Sanctuary
address: Jl. Monkey Forest, Ubud, Kecamatan Ubud, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80571
note_from_owner:
The Monkey Forest in Ubud is a lush, enchanting sanctuary nestled in the heart of Bali. Officially known as the Sacred Monkey Forest Sanctuary, this sprawling reserve is home to hundreds of playful long-tailed macaques.
It serves not only as a wildlife haven but also as a site of spiritual and cultural significance, with ancient temples and sacred groves scattered throughout the forest.
Managed by the Management of Monkey Forest and Padangtegal village, the Monkey Forest is both a popular tourist destination and a vital center for conservation and local heritage, offering visitors a unique blend of natural beauty and cultural depth.

note_from_owner: This waterfall falls from a steep cliff and is surrounded by dense forest, so it is no less beautiful if you just want to admire it from a distance. The shallow natural pool located in the river is perfect for playing in the water and soaking for hours while enjoying the peaceful natural atmosphere, and the best part is that the location is not far from Ubud, about 30 minutes and only takes 7 minutes on foot from the parking area. Temesi Waterfall is also a suitable place for freewed photos, because there are many charming photo spots here, and for those who want to take freewed photos, please make a reservation in advance and for freewed photos it will be open from 06.00 to 08.30 only.

title: Setia Darma House of Mask and Puppets
address: Jalan Tegal Bingin, Banjar Tengkulak Tengah, Kemenuh, Sukawati, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80582
street: Jalan Tegal Bingin, Banjar Tengkulak Tengah
note_from_owner:
The House of Masks and Puppets was initiated by Mr. Hadi Sunyoto, a businessman and cultural enthusiast assisted by the late Mr. Agustinus Prayitno, a lover of antiques and culture. Both of them has been collecting masks and puppets from different regions in Indonesia for the past years. Mr. Hadi decided to create a space to collect, preserve and spread the knowledge of the art form of masks and puppets. As a result, the House of Masks and Puppets was open 2006.
The use of the word house for the space is used to signify the space as a place for activities, just like a house is.

title: Kecak & Fire Dance at Tanah Gajah, Ubud
address: Tanah Gajah, a Resort by Hadiprana, Jl. Raya Goa Gajah, Tengkulak Kaja, Kecamatan Ubud, Bali 80571
street: Tanah Gajah, a Resort by Hadiprana, Jl. Raya Goa Gajah
note_from_owner:
PERFORMED EVERY TUESDAY & FRIDAY EVENING AT 19:00
*Also performing every Sunday evening at 19:00 until 3 September 2023*

Ubud is the cultural centre of Bali and is famous for its dances, and Tanah Gajah Ubud is proud to host a dance troupe of between fifty and seventy boys and men from the local community who perform the Kecak dance.

The spectacular 30 minute-long Balinese Kecak and fire dance performances are held at Tanah Gajah Ubud's candle-lit outdoor amphitheatre, , followed by an opportunity for guests to take photos with the talented performers before heading to The Tempayan restaurant for the Royal Rijsttafel dinner experience.

ementerian Agraria dan Tata Ruang/ Badan Pertanahan Nasional

Sesuai Peraturan Presiden Republik Indonesia Nomor 17 Tahun 2015 tentang Kementerian Agraria dan Tata Ruang, Kementerian Agraria dan Tata Ruang (ATR) mempunyai tugas menyelenggarakan urusan pemerintahan di bidang agraria/pertanahan dan tata ruang untuk membantu Presiden dalam menyelenggarakan pemerintahan negara.
Dalam melaksanakan tugasnya, Kementerian ATR menyelenggarakan fungsi:

perumusan, penetapan, dan pelaksanaan kebijakan di bidang tata ruang, infrastruktur keagrariaan/pertanahan, hubungan hukum keagrariaan/pertanahan, penataan agraria/pertanahan, pengadaan tanah, pengendalian pemanfaatan ruang dan penguasaan tanah, serta penanganan masalah agraria/pertanahan, pemanfaatan

title: Puri Kauhan Ubud
address: Gg. Beji No.35, Ubud, Kecamatan Ubud, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80571
note_from_owner:
Puri Kauhan Ubud is one of Balinese cultural heritage which is located in the cultural heart of the Island of the Gods in Ubud, Gianyar.

Established since the 19th century, Puri Kauhan Ubud has become part of the history of Bali and Indonesia. Puri Kauhan Ubud keeps historical records, cultural stories, and Balinese literature in manuscripts made from coconut tree leaves – also known as Lontar.

We invite all parties to explore the history and culture of Bali and Indonesia at Puri Kauhan Ubud.

note_from_owner:
Bali Dewata, kami adalah perusahaan yang bergerak di seni dekoratif dan proyek kreatif di Desa Silakarang, 4 km selatan Ubud.

Secara historis, sejak abad ke-16 desa kami merupakan tempat tumbuhnya seniman ukiran dan arsitek tradisional yang mengerjakan seni dekoratif berkualitas tinggi di banyak Pura dan Istana di Bali.

Bali Dewata dimulai ketika kakek kami mengerjakan furniture kayu, gapura di Puri Klungkung serta beberapa Pura di Bali. Bali Dewata dengan antusias melanjutkan legasi itu, mengeksplorasi dan menciptakan sesuatu yang baru tanpa meninggalkan nilai-nilai lama.

Saat ini karya seni berkualitas tinggi bermedia kayu, batu, fiber glass dan beton sudah tersebar di Bali, serta dikirim ke seluruh dunia melalui kargo laut dan udara.

street: G753+2F7, Jl. Raya Sanggingan Jl. Raya Campuhan
note_from_owner:
Founded in 1975, the Neka Art Museum (NAM) is a cornerstone of cultural heritage in Bali. NAM spotlight both traditional and contemporary arts. NAM has an impressive collection of paintings, sculptures, photography, and Keris.

Established by JMK Suteja Neka and NGM Srimin, the museum celebrates Bali’s artistic diversity with works from Balinese, Indonesian, Asian, and Western artists inspired by the island’s natural beauty and vibrant culture.

Under PM Kardi Suteja and his family’s leadership, NAM has undergone a major revitalization with building renovations, reorganization of collections, and new cultural programs. Visitors can now enjoy hands-on workshops like Keris Making and Balinese Painting Classes, among others.

title: Agung Rai Museum of Art
address: Jl. Raya Pengosekan Ubud, Ubud, Kecamatan Ubud, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80571
note_from_owner:
The ARMA Foundation in Bali, Indonesia, was established in 1996 to promote and preserve Balinese art and culture. The Foundation is the administrative arm for a complex that includes a world class museum, a center for visual and performing arts including a dance and music Sanggar, or informal school. Hundreds of children, teenagers and adults have benefited from the ARMA Sanggar, which ARMA makes available without cost to local families. Many of these children have gone on to perform in their communities as skilled dancers and musicians. But now the continuation of the ARMA Sanggar program is under serious pressure, due to the declining income from donations of tourists.
